<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 9800 MODEL - TESTING ENGINE BRAKE RELAY (CAT
        3406C ONLY)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING ENGINE BRAKE RELAY (CAT 3406C ONLY)</title>
        <table id="t0403524" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Engine Brake Relay (Caterpillar 3406C Only)</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="s1t6" align="center"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove engine brake relay from connector (654). Key ON - measure voltage to ground at
                                circuit 94C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 94C from warning light relay connector
                                (443), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove connector (627) from controller. At (654) use test lead to jumper circuit 94J
                                to 94C. Key ON - At connector (627) measure voltage to ground at terminal K1.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 94J, Yellow wire between connectors (627) and (654), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With relay removed, connect 12 volt test lead to terminal 85 and ground to terminal
                                86. Note if relay energizes with an audible click.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Relay energized?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next Step</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With relay energized, measure resistance between terminals 30 and 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remove 12 volt test leads and measure resistance between relay terminals 30 and 87A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Engine Brake Relay circuit is working properly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
